description:
&lt;p&gt;Ward 25 is a busy, proactive renal ward that works closely with colleagues in the Renal Dialysis Unit, Renal satellite centres and Renal Specialist Nurses. We are looking for experienced Healthcare Assistants to join our highly committed team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward 25 has an excellent reputation for being a very supportive and friendly team. We realise our staff are our greatest asset and as such we are looking for senior health care assistants that are good team players, enthusiastic learners, and above all caring and compassionate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is essential the candidates expressing an interest have the ability to work flexibly as part of the team and able to use excellent communication skills to provide compassionate care in sometimes challenging environment. Commitment to working as part of a multi professional team dedicated to delivering quality patient centred care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like more information regarding this opportunity or a virtual visit to the unit please contact …&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Diane Till Ward Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Daine.TILL@lthtr.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01772 522522&lt;/p&gt;
